President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Dawn O'Connell as Assistant Secretary for Preparedness and Response at the Department of Health and Human Services. O'Connell is currently serving as Senior Counselor to the Secretary for COVID-19, where she coordinates the department's response to the pandemic. She previously worked as the Director of the Coalition for Epidemic Preparedness and Innovation's US Office and as Senior Counselor to Secretary Sylvia Burwell at the US Department of Health and Human Services during the Obama Administration. O'Connell has a background in global health and humanitarian issues and holds degrees from Vanderbilt University and Tulane University School of Law.